Ulaire Nelya, LOM<br>
Bill Ferney, Swarthy Sneering Fellow<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(855)">Savagery to Match Their Numbers</a><br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(36)">Spies of Saruman</a><br>
Uruk Captain<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(32)">Saruman&#39;s Frost</a><br>
Lurtz&#39;s Sword<br>
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> This deck is one of my most successful.  There is a ton of strategy writing, so make sure you read it all.  It is very enlightening, if not blatenly obvious...<br>
<br>
The sites.  number 1 is obvious, number 2 because I think it is the best Uruk site 2.  Exert to power up is a great ability, and you can also cause exertions on the opponent with what I like to call &quot;an exertion race.&quot;  Clever Huh?  Site 3 is just for playing free weapons and companions, that is all.  Hollin is the best uruk site 4.  Period.  I couldnt decide what site to play next, so I chose the Bridge.  Site 6 is simply for healing Frodo, because he usually takes alot of exertions and archery wounds... good old Frodo.  Since I have 3 rangers, i play silverlode banks to counter decks that use all Dwarves or Hobbits.  Site 8 is simply for when the opposing player is ahead, as I love the high twilight for my uruks and would never myself go to this site, unless the opponent was playing it also.  Slopes of Amon Hen is a gosh darnit good site 9 for uruks.  This site has caused many victories for me, as I have effectively swarmed  with uruks many times with this site.  Strategy: use this site and sarumans frost.  If you have played effectively with your uruks, you have probably kille at least two companions and wounded many others.  Swarm with this site and watch as frodo cant survive with his strength knocked down 2.  This is how I won a tournament game once.   <br>
<br>
With this deck,  the shadow and fellowship are both very strong, so going first usually isnt a problem.  If you know you&#39;re playing Nazgul, bid 1 (to use the pony-I hate nazgul sword dam +1).  Otherwise, bid 2 and go first if you win.  The fellowship is centered around Gandalf.  With his 4 Servants, he can usually help your other strong companions win skirmishes, or at least prevent them from being overwhelmed.  Servant is one of my favorite cards.  It is so effective and flexible that it allows you to use it with other companions other than just Gandalf.  They are even better with his staff, as they are free to use.  The other companions are pretty powerful, as the jump through the dangerous underground sites are made less dangerous with them.  Borimir with armor only takes two wounds with a fierce Balrog, and if you happen to get all 4 Servants out by site 5, you can overwhelm him with Gandalf or Aragorn (insert &quot;yeah right&quot; here).  <br>
<br>
My other stuff in the deck is pretty much common and self explanatory.  Thror&#39;s Map, to avoid dangerous sites like The Ford, Discard every Ally, or skip the Archery phase, etc. Aragorn and Borimir&#39;s weapons for killing stuff and less overwhelmtion (is that a word?), Sting and Glamdring for strength boosters and twilight removal, Mr. Gorn&#39;s Bow because it works wonders with ARV and anything in general, O elbereth because it is a totally badass card that plays for free and gives a strength bonus as well as a free  nazgul skirmish cancel, Gwemegil for anti Nazgulness and added card cycling, PATHS because it is awesome with ARV and is a life saver, Sleep to get rid of annoying conditions (what else?), Greenleaf because he&#39;s a total stud and his archery can also be a lifesaver, ARV because I have 3 rangers in the deck and it helps a ton with those late, high-twilight rivers, Flaming Brands because Nazgul are insanely powerful and I dont want them winning skirmishes (also because it plays for free and gives +1 str. no matter what), Athelas because it is a really good card to heal or get rid of those pesky shadow conditions like Blade Tip, Elrond because he is also a total badass and he can draw cards (if he fights at site 3, that is good too)<br>
<br>
For the shadow side, I play mostly Uruks.  I put some Nazgul in, like Cantea, who can get rid of weapons, and Nelya, who plays your sites.  I basically use the old &quot;power up a Uruk then use LBC to kill companions,&quot; and it works very well.  I cannot help but reinerate the obvoius, such as making Lurtz fierce with another Uruk, and discarding Saruman&#39;s Ambition when appropriate, and canceling ARV and other events with Uruk Scout and stuff.  I threw in Bill Ferny and Sarumans Frost just in case I get the chance to use them and overwhelm Frodo.  I used to not play with Sarumans Frost until Played at site 9 in a tournament, and overwhelmed Frodo because of it.  Now I think it is important to play at least one in every Uruk deck, if not for anything but for site 9.  I think Troop of Uruk Hai is my favorite Uruk minion.  Everyone plays with weapons, and these guys take advantage of it.  Use Beyond The Height of Men to get rid of Uruks biggest headache: Armor.  Use Cantea to rid weapons of the opposing fellowship, and spies of saruman to rid yourself of that annoying archery phase.  Play Uruk Captain to use Uruks from your discard pile, etc. etc. etc.  <br>
 <br>
I&#39;ve read that alot of people dont like to use the Balrog.  I, however, am a firm believer in his importance.  Every place that I&#39;ve played, people want to double jump from sites 4 to 6, and often they give a ton of twilight to do this.  I play the balrog at site 5, because even if he doesnt do much, he still leaves me with a ton to use if the fellowship moves again.  Plus, there&#39;s always the chance that they cant get their underground protection out in time, in which case the Balrog could cause massive damage.  One last closing note about the Balrog: He is Power 17, damage +1, fierce and  is pullable and plays for 6!  Definately worth a card slot in my humble opinion.  <br>
<br>
Thanks for reading my long-winded strategy section and I would appreciate helpful, constructive, non-biased comments please... or just tell me how stupid my deck is!          </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=23721"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=23721" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
